from scipy.interpolate import interp1d

x1 = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 45])
y1 = np.array([1, 8, 27, 64, 125, 91125])

# Create an interpolation function
f = interp1d(x1, y1, kind='linear', fill_value='extrapolate')

# Define x_new

# Interpolate y values
y_interp = f(x_new)

# Print the result
print(y_interp)

#!/usr/bin/env bash
###############################################
# Script para backups de equipamentos Ubiquiti
# Criado por Sergio Lenaz
###############################################

# Diretórios de origem e destino
origem="/home/listaips.txt"
destino="/home/paineis/$(date +%d-%m-%Y)"
log="/home/logs/ubiquiti.log"

# Cria o diretório de destino
mkdir -p "$destino"

# Registra a hora de início no log
INICIO=$(date +%d-%m-%Y_%H:%M:%S)
echo "#####*************** Backup iniciado em $INICIO ***************#####" >> "$log"

# Loop para fazer backup com base na lista de IPs
while IFS=',' read -r nome ip usuario senha; do
    # Tenta fazer o backup e registra o resultado no log
    if sshpass -p "$senha" ssh "$usuario@$ip" -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no "cat /tmp/system.cfg" > "$destino/$nome-$ip-backup-$(date +%d-%m-%Y).cfg" 2>/dev/null; then
        FIM=$(date +%d-%m-%Y_%H:%M:%S)
        echo "O backup de $nome-$ip foi efetuado com sucesso em $FIM" >> "$log"
    else
        echo "Ocorreu um erro ao realizar o backup de $nome-$ip em $(date +%d-%m-%Y_%H:%M:%S)" >> "$log"
    fi
done < "$origem"

# Deleta os arquivos que estão com tamanho 0k (backups que geraram erros)
find "$destino" -type f -size 0 -name '*.cfg' -exec rm {} \;

# Deleta os arquivos criados há mais de 7 dias
find "$destino" -type f -ctime +7 -name '*.cfg' -exec rm {} \;

import random
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot_queens(board):
    n = len(board)

    # Crear un tablero de ajedrez con casillas blancas y negras
    chessboard = [[(i + j) % 2 for i in range(n)] for j in range(n)]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.matshow(chessboard, cmap='binary')

    # Colocar las reinas en el tablero
    for i in range(n):
        ax.text(board[i] - 1, i, '♛', ha='center', va='center', color='brown', fontsize=14)

    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

def order_crossover(parent1, parent2):
    size = len(parent1)
    start, end = sorted([random.randint(0, size-1), random.randint(0, size-1)])
    offspring = [-1] * size
    offspring[start:end] = parent1[start:end]

    j = end
    for i in range(size):
        if parent2[(i+end)%size] not in offspring:
            offspring[j] = parent2[(i+end)%size]
            j = (j+1) % size

    return offspring

def count_queen_collisions(board):
    n = len(board)
    collisions = 0

    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i + 1, n):
            if board[i] == board[j] or abs(board[i] - board[j]) == abs(i - j):
                collisions += 1

    return collisions

def mutate_queens(board):
    n = len(board)
    new_board = list(board)
    random.shuffle(new_board)  # Se reorganizan aleatoriamente las posiciones de las reinas
    return new_board

def generate_child_without_collisions(parent1, parent2, num_attempts=100):
    best_child = None
    best_collisions = float('inf')

    for _ in range(num_attempts):
        child = order_crossover(parent1, parent2)
        collisions = count_queen_collisions(child)

        if collisions == 0:  # Si no hay colisiones, el hijo es óptimo
            return child, collisions

        # Intentar mutar el hijo para reducir colisiones
        mutated_child = mutate_queens(child)
        mutated_collisions = count_queen_collisions(mutated_child)

        if mutated_collisions < best_collisions:
            best_child = mutated_child
            best_collisions = mutated_collisions

    return best_child, best_collisions

parent1 = [4, 2, 5, 7, 1, 8, 3, 6]
parent2 = [2, 5, 3, 1, 8, 7, 4, 6]
plot_queens(parent1)
print("Padre 2")
plot_queens(parent2)
best_child, best_collisions = generate_child_without_collisions(parent1, parent2)
print("Número de colisiones entre reinas en el mejor descendiente:", best_collisions)
print("Descendiente con el menor número de colisiones:", best_child)
plot_queens(best_child)

import random
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot_queens(board):
    n = len(board)

    # Crear un tablero de ajedrez con casillas blancas y negras
    chessboard = [[(i + j) % 2 for i in range(n)] for j in range(n)]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.matshow(chessboard, cmap='binary')

    # Colocar las reinas en el tablero
    for i in range(n):
        ax.text(board[i] - 1, i, '♛', ha='center', va='center', color='brown', fontsize=14)

    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

def pmx_crossover(parent1, parent2):
    size = len(parent1)
    start, end = sorted([random.randint(0, size-1), random.randint(0, size-1)])
    offspring = [-1] * size
    offspring[start:end] = parent1[start:end]

    for i in range(start, end):
        if parent2[i] not in offspring:
            j = i
            while start <= j < end:
                j = parent2.index(parent1[j])
            offspring[j] = parent2[i]

    for i in range(size):
        if offspring[i] == -1:
            offspring[i] = parent2[i]

    return offspring

def count_queen_collisions(board):
    n = len(board)
    collisions = 0

    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i + 1, n):
            if board[i] == board[j] or abs(board[i] - board[j]) == abs(i - j):
                collisions += 1

    return collisions

def mutate_queens(board):
    n = len(board)
    new_board = list(board)
    random.shuffle(new_board)  # Se reorganizan aleatoriamente las posiciones de las reinas
    return new_board

def generate_child_without_collisions(parent1, parent2, num_attempts=100):
    best_child = None
    best_collisions = float('inf')

    for _ in range(num_attempts):
        child = pmx_crossover(parent1, parent2)
        collisions = count_queen_collisions(child)

        if collisions == 0:  # Si no hay colisiones, el hijo es óptimo
            return child, collisions

        # Intentar mutar el hijo para reducir colisiones
        mutated_child = mutate_queens(child)
        mutated_collisions = count_queen_collisions(mutated_child)

        if mutated_collisions < best_collisions:
            best_child = mutated_child
            best_collisions = mutated_collisions

    return best_child, best_collisions

parent1 = [4, 2, 5, 7, 1, 8, 3, 6]
parent2 = [2, 5, 3, 1, 8, 7, 4, 6]
plot_queens(parent1)
print("Padre 2")
plot_queens(parent2)
best_child, best_collisions = generate_child_without_collisions(parent1, parent2)
print("Número de colisiones entre reinas en el mejor descendiente:", best_collisions)
print("Descendiente con el menor número de colisiones:", best_child)
plot_queens(best_child)

	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_12", 19},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_13", 20},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_14", 21},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_15", 22},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_16", 23},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_17", 24},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_18", 25},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_19", 26},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_20", 28},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_21", 29},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_22", 30},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_23", 31},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_24", 32},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_25", 33},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_26", 34},
	{"radioactiveWasteBarrel_27", 35},
}
rednet.open("bottom")

while true do
	currentLowestTank = 0
	currentLowestPercentage = 0
	totalPercentage = 0
	for i, tank in pairs(Tanks) do
		 tnk = peripheral.wrap(Tanks[i][1])
		 percentage = tnk.getFilledPercentage()
		 if currentLowestPercentage <= percentage and percentage < Threashhold then
			currentLowestTank = i
			currentLowestPercentage = percentage
			totalPercentage = totalPercentage + percentage
		end
	end
	
	for i, tank in pairs(Tanks) do
		 if currentLowestTank == i then
			rednet.send(Tanks[i][2], "FALSE", "WASTE_MANAGEMENT")
		else
			rednet.send(Tanks[i][2], "TRUE", "WASTE_MANAGEMENT")
		end
	end
	term.clear()
	term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
	term.write("Filled: " .. (totalPercentage/#Tanks)*100 .. "%")
	term.setCursorPos(1, 2)
	term.write("Filling: " .. Tanks[currentLowestTank][1])
	Monitor.clear()
	Monitor.setCursorPos(1, 1)
	Monitor.write("Filled: " .. (totalPercentage/#Tanks)*100 .. "%")
	Monitor.setCursorPos(1, 2)
	Monitor.write("Filling: " .. Tanks[currentLowestTank][1])
	
	if icon then
		w,h = term.getSize()
		term.setCursorPos(w, h)
		term.write("*")
		w,h = Monitor.getSize()
		Monitor.setCursorPos(w, h)
		Monitor.write("*")
	else
		w,h = term.getSize()
		term.setCursorPos(w, h)
		term.write(" ")
		w,h = Monitor.getSize()
		Monitor.setCursorPos(w, h)
		Monitor.write(" ")
	end
	icon = not icon
	os.sleep(0.5)
end

function left()
    
    turtle.turnLeft()
    direction = direction - 1
    if direction == 0 then
        direction = 4
    end
    saveDirection()
    
end

function right()
    
    turtle.turnRight()
    direction = direction + 1
    if direction == 5 then
        direction = 1
    end
    saveDirection()
    
end

-----------------------------------------------MAIN-----------------------------------------------------------------------

rednet.open('left')
while true do

id, instruction = rednet.receive()
id, repeats = rednet.receive()
for i = 1, repeats do

    if instruction == 'forward' then
        turtle.forward()
    elseif instruction == 'up' then
        turtle.up()
    elseif instruction == 'down' then 
        if turtle.detectDown() then
            turtle.digDown()
        end
        turtle.down()
    elseif instruction == 'left' then
        left()
    else 
        right()
    end

end

end

            {"Grass", "4722588177"}, {"Ice", "3823766459"},
            {"Marble", "62967586"}, {"Metal", "62967586"},
            {"Sand", "152572215"}
        }
        
        function texture(ins, id)
            for _, v in pairs(faces) do
                local texture = Instance.new("Texture", ins)
                texture.ZIndex = 2147483647
                texture.Texture = "rbxassetid://" .. id
                texture.Face = Enum.NormalId[v]
                texture.Color3 = ins.Color
                texture.Transparency = ins.Transparency
            end
        end
        
        for _, part in pairs(workspace:GetDescendants()) do
            if part:IsA("BasePart") then
                for _, v in pairs(materials) do
                    if part.Material.Name == v[1] then
                        texture(part, v[2])
                        part.Material = "SmoothPlastic"
                    end
                end
            end
        end

title: Programa C - Conta hotel
Linq Problem
Untitled
Python from ChatGPT - Print 0 to 4096
content:
# Python program written by ChatGPT to print 
# the numbers from 0 to 4096 in columns.

# Define the range of numbers
start = 0
end = 4096

# Print the column headers
print("Decimal   Binary       Hexadecimal")
print("-" * 32)

# Iterate through the numbers and print them in three columns
for num in range(start, end + 1):
    binary_num = bin(num)[2:]
    hexadecimal_num = hex(num)[2:].upper()
    print(f"{num:7}   {binary_num:12}   {hexadecimal_num}")
